### Welcome! I'm Shreyas Meher. This site showcases my work in computational linguistics and political analysis. Feel free to explore and connect with me!
:::

### Research Interests

> Large Language Models (LLMs), Internet Censorship, Developmental Economics, Political Conflict and Violence

### Currently at

> **The University of Texas at Dallas** <br> **Research Assistant** <br> *ConfliBERT Project with Dr. Patrick Brandt (2022-present)* <br> Dr. Pengfei Zhang (2022-present) <br> Dr. Lauren Pinson (2021-present) <br> Dr. Jonas Bunte (2020-2021)

> **Teaching Assistant** <br> *Dr. Vito D'Orazio (2020-2021)* <br> Dr. Richard Scotch (2020)

### Key Projects

> **ConfliBERT Research Lab** <br> A groundbreaking project exploring political conflict and violence using pre-trained language models. [Learn More](link-to-project-details-or-paper)

> **Dissertation on Censorship in Democracies and Autocracies** <br> An in-depth analysis focusing on electoral accountability with case studies in India and China. [Read More](link-to-dissertation-summary)
